8e57176d94b6a44dcd1336849731fa5bc79c2e53af21b47e5a271f012270f5b1 ``` Here's how to use it: **Base URL:** `https://api.datamartgh.shop/api/developer` ‚Üó **Auth header:** add `X-API-Key: <your key>` to every request. **Key endpoints:** - Check balance: `GET /balance` - Buy data: `POST /purchase` with `{phoneNumber, network, capacity, gateway:"wallet"}` - Bulk orders (up to 50): `POST /bulk-purchase` - Check order: `GET /order-status/:reference` **Networks:** YELLO (MTN), TELECEL, AT_PREMIUM. The API pays from your wallet, so keep it topped up at https://www.datamartgh.shop/topup ‚Üó . Also send an `X-Idempotency-Key` header on each request so retries never double-charge. Full docs and examples here: https://www.datamartgh.shop/api-doc ‚Üó
Here are the available data packages and prices (GHS) per network, Cyril üëç **MTN (YELLO):** 1GB=‚Çµ4 | 2GB=‚Çµ8 | 3GB=‚Çµ12 | 4GB=‚Çµ16 | 5GB=‚Çµ20 | 6GB=‚Çµ24 | 8GB=‚Çµ32 | 10GB=‚Çµ39 | 15GB=‚Çµ57 | 20GB=‚Çµ76.50 | 25GB=‚Çµ96 | 30GB=‚Çµ115 | 40GB=‚Çµ157 | 50GB=‚Çµ185 | 100GB=‚Çµ407 **AirtelTigo (AT_PREMIUM):** 1GB=‚Çµ3.95 | 2GB=‚Çµ8.35 | 3GB=‚Çµ13.25 | 4GB=‚Çµ16.50 | 5GB=‚Çµ19.50 | 6GB=‚Çµ23.50 | 8GB=‚Çµ30.50 | 10GB=‚Çµ38.50 | 12GB=‚Çµ45.50 | 15GB=‚Çµ57.50 | 25GB=‚Çµ95 | 30GB=‚Çµ115 | 40GB=‚Çµ151 | 50GB=‚Çµ190 **Telecel:** 5GB=‚Çµ19.50 | 8GB=‚Çµ34.64 | 10GB=‚Çµ36.50 | 12GB=‚Çµ43.70 | 15GB=‚Çµ52.85 | 20GB=‚Çµ69.80 | 25GB=‚Çµ86.75 | 30GB=‚Çµ103.70 | 40GB=‚Çµ137.60 | 50GB=‚Çµ171.50 | 100GB=‚Çµ341 To buy via the API, use the `capacity` value (e.g. `1`, `5`, `10`) and the matching `network` code (`YELLO`, `AT_PREMIUM`, `TELECEL`) in your POST /purchase call. Full details at https://www.datamartgh.shop/api-doc ‚Üó
I‚Äôll update orderController.js so that when a customer tracks an order (by reference or phone), the system pings DataMart for the latest status and updates your database accordingly.
Sure Cyril! Here's a clean example for your `orderController.js`: ```javascript const axios = require('axios'); const DATAMART_API = 'https://api.datamartgh.shop/api/developer' ‚Üó ; const API_KEY = 'your_api_key_here'; async function trackAndUpdateOrder(reference) { try { // Ping DataMart for latest status const { data } = await axios.get( `${DATAMART_API}/order-status/${reference}`, { headers: { 'X-API-Key': API_KEY } } ); // Update your own DB with the latest status await Order.findOneAndUpdate( { reference }, { status: data.status, updatedAt: new Date() }, { new: true } ); return data; } catch (error) { console.error('Order track error:', error.message); throw error; } } ``` A few tips: - Replace `Order.findOneAndUpdate` with whatever your DB model/ORM is (Mongoose, Sequelize, etc.) - The `reference` is the `MN-...` reference you get back when you POST to `/purchase` - You can call this on demand (when a customer tracks) or set a cron to poll pending orders periodically Full response shape and status values are in the docs: https://www.datamartgh.shop/api-doc ‚Üó
